### Implementation details

`cmd_completion.go`:
1. `flag.NewFlagSet("config completion", ...)` with `--context`, `--json`, `--ghost`
2. Parse config file using existing `config.YANGSchema()` + `config.NewParser(schema)`
3. Create `editor.NewCompleter()`, call `completer.SetTree(tree)`
4. Split `--context` on `.` to get `contextPath []string`
5. Call `completer.Complete(input, contextPath)` or `completer.GhostText(input, contextPath)`
6. Output as text table or JSON

The `Completer` is already a standalone type — no TUI dependency needed. This is just wiring it to CLI.

### Functional tests

Add `.ci` tests in `test/config/completion/` (new dir) to exercise the command:

| Test | What it validates |
|------|-------------------|
| `root-commands.ci` | Empty input returns editor commands |
| `bgp-set-keywords.ci` | `set ` at bgp context shows YANG children |
| `peer-fields.ci` | `set ` inside peer context shows peer-as, address |
| `value-hints.ci` | `set router-id ` shows value type hint |
| `ghost-text.ci` | `--ghost` flag returns ghost text |
| `json-output.ci` | `--json` flag returns valid JSON array |
| `list-keys.ci` | `edit peer ` shows existing peer IPs from config |

These use the existing `.ci` test format (`expect=stdout:contains=`, `expect=exit:code=0`).

## Completer Bugs (in scope)

Tests exposed these bugs in `internal/component/config/editor/completer.go`:

| Bug | Description | Test |
|-----|-------------|------|
| Missing `environment` | `environment` not exposed as root-level completion target | `cli-completion-env-*.ci` |
| Missing `plugin` | `plugin` not exposed as root-level completion target | `cli-completion-plugin-external.ci` |
| `show`/`edit` missing leaves | `show+` and `edit+` only return containers, should also return leaves | `cli-completion-show-targets.ci`, `cli-completion-bgp-edit.ci` |
| Set-path list key navigation | `set bgp peer 1.1.1.1 ` should descend into peer context, shows list keys instead | `cli-completion-set-deep-path.ci` |

These are bugs in the Completer, not the test infrastructure. The tests express correct expectations.

## Test Infrastructure

| Change | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `test/ui/` directory | New test directory for UI/completion functional tests |
| `ze-test bgp ui` command | New test runner subcommand using `EncodingTests` runner |
| `make ze-ui-test` | Individual make target for UI tests |
| `--input` flag with `+` encoding | `+` = space, avoids shell quoting issues in test runner |
| `--context` with `/` separator | `/` = path separator, avoids `strings.Fields()` splitting |

